{{Infobox journal | title = Historical Journal of Film, Radio and Television | cover = Historical journal of film, radio and television-2012, no. 2.jpeg | image_size = 200px | editor = | discipline = [[Media history]] | language = English | formernames = | abbreviation = | publisher = Routledge | country = United Kingdom | frequency = Quarterly | history = 1980-present | openaccess = | license = | impact = | impact-year = | website = | JSTOR = | OCLC = | LCCN = | CODEN = | ISSN = 0143-9685 | eISSN = }}
The '''''Historical Journal of Film, Radio and Television''''' ({{ISSN|0143-9685}}; E-ISSN 1465-3451) is an [[academic journal]] dedicated to the study of media history. It is published quarterly by [[Routledge]] on behalf of the [[International Association for Media and History]]. The current editor-in-chief is [[James Chapman (media historian)|James Chapman]].
This interdisciplinary journal considers mass media from the perspective of historians and social scientists. It covers the impact of mass communications on 20th century history.
